  "brief": "<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> Market Overview</h2>\n\nFutures are ripping higher across the board with SPY up +1.39% to $733.83 and NASDAQ leading at +2.08%. VIX dropping -2.23% to 28.07 signals some risk-on appetite returning as Iran war headlines suggest potential ceasefire momentum. Tech and industrials are driving the rally while energy gets hammered on crude oil weakness.\n\n<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> What to Watch</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Initial Jobless Claims</strong> - Multiple employment data points at 12:30 ET could shift Fed expectations</li>\n<li><strong>Iran War Headlines</strong> - Any ceasefire progress will crush VIX and pump risk assets</li>\n<li><strong>Productivity & Labor Costs</strong> - Fed's inflation calculus depends on these 12:30 ET releases</li>\n<li><strong>Energy Sector Collapse</strong> - XLE down -4.12% on potential war resolution, watch for oversold bounce</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> Sector Rotation</h2>\n\nClassic risk-on rotation underway with tech (+2.66%) and industrials (+2.59%) leading while energy craters -4.12% on war resolution hopes. Utilities also weak at -1.42% as growth stocks reclaim momentum. This is textbook geopolitical uncertainty unwind - growth over value, cyclicals over defensives.\n\n<div class=\"callout callout-green\"><div class=\"callout-label\">✦ Bull Case</div>Iran ceasefire breaks VIX below 25, unlocks massive short covering rally in growth names. Oil collapse boosts consumer spending power into summer.</div>\n\n<div class=\"callout callout-amber\"><div class=\"callout-label\">⚡ Key Driver</div>Trump-Xi summit headlines could provide additional catalyst. Watch for any trade deal progress or semiconductor restrictions updates.</div>\n\n<div class=\"callout callout-red\"><div class=\"callout-label\">⚠ Bear Case</div>VIX still elevated at 28 - one bad headline reverses this entire move. Jobs data could reignite Fed hawkishness if too strong.</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> Levels That Matter</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>SPY $740</strong> - Key resistance, breakout targets $750+ quickly</li>\n<li><strong>QQQ $700</strong> - Psychological level, clear it for $720 test</li>\n<li><strong>VIX 25</strong> - Break below signals real risk-on regime change</li>\n<li><strong>XLE $85</strong> - Oversold energy bounce level, dead cat or real reversal</li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr>\n<p><em>Not a prediction. A preparation. Make your plan before the bell.</em></p>"
